"Never be silenced."
"It is a direct transcript from one of the letters," said the Philadelphia artist.
"When I think about it, I get goose bumps."
Manning has not visited the exhibition in person - as predicted in the comic book - but when she does, she will be welcomed in the center of the room with her masks, her own genomic forms, sorted as a crowd of Protestants.
This was also the purpose of the exhibition, including the nearly 160 cm tall statue of Maningo, on which her genetic haplogroups are recorded in pencil.
