Vice-President of the Russian Government Vitala Mutko said that it would not take long to implement the remaining World Anti-Doping Agency (WADA) criteria and re-establishment of the Russian Anti-Doping Agency (RUSADA).
‘Part of the criteria of the new plan has already been completed and RUSADA has already acquired the right to planning and testing in cooperation with the British Anti-Doping Agency (UKAD).
